**Sunday Group Ride Notice and Rules**

Join us for our Sunday group ride! Here are the key details and rules to ensure a pleasant ride for everyone:

1. **Being On Time**: It is essential to BE ON TIME! We will start the ride sharp at the set time.

2. **No Drop Social Ride**: This ride is a no-drop, social ride. The main group will maintain a pace and there will be a few regroup points during the ride (e.g., before complicate route with multiple turns or after a long climb.)

3. ** Experience Level**: The pace will be comfortable for advance beginner with climbing experience. Ensure you have the necessary experience and fitness to participate.

4. **Group Ride Etiquette**: Familiarize yourself with basic group ride hand signals and unwritten ethics.

5. **Route Knowledge**: If you decide to ride at a faster pace and get separated from the group, know the route and be prepared to find your own way home.

6. **Newcomer Responsibility**: If you plan to bring friend(s), please ensure you download the map and stay with your friend(s), they are your responsibility. The main group will not delay the ride.

7. **Safety Gear**: Please bring a helmet, spare tubes, a pump or CO2 cartridges, water, and all necessary supplies.

8. **Participation Acknowledgment**: Participation in this event/ride is voluntary. Participants acknowledge the risks and/or dangers associated with cycling and are thus responsible for their own safety.

We look forward to enjoyable ride. See you on the road!

title: 往西，越过天际(Skyline)吧骚年
description:
路线:
Redwood Townhall 集合 - OLH  爬坡 - Loma 邱林 - Pescadero 小镇 - San Gregorio 小店 - Tunitas 爬坡 - Kings Mountain 下山

适合夏天的避暑路线 credit @Steve
有两个大爬坡，分别是大家熟悉的 Old La Honda，和很多人熟悉的从Bike Hut开始的Tunitas Creek Rd

预计总时间6 hours

本路线也叫避暑路线，因为在树林中穿行，或是海边吹风。起始从Redwood Townhall出发，这也是在 [旧金山湾区骑行路线 第一章 练](https://rangerway.com/way/cycling-routes-at-bay-area) 介绍过的OLH老本田训练路线的起始点，可以把这个地方看作是湾区骑行的一个hub，因为很多骑行路线无论是转山还是休闲骑还是辣堡团，都会以这里为起点或者经过这里。
这一路上有很多可以驻足休息的好玩的地方，像Pescadero小镇和San Gregorio小店，还有下图的 The Bike Hut。一路的风景也有很多令我初见惊艳的地方。期待您也去探索一番，发现不一样的景色。

title: Old La Honda Winter Time Trail (Bridge to Traffic light)
description:
Old La Honda Winter Time Trail (Bridge to Traffic light)

⌚️Meet by: Saturday 11/1 9:00AM

📍Meet at: Burgess park / 701 Laurel Street, 701 Laurel Street, Menlo Park, California 94025

🗺️Route: https://www.strava.com/clubs/1157973/group_events/2143574

📝Note: *We're doing TT from Bridge to traffic light only. MAKE SURE STOPPING BY THE RED LIGHT. You can use 'OLH Full segment time' minus 'OLH Mile 3 to end' to get the final result.

1. Warm up: from burgess park to bottom of OLH.
2. Race pace ride up OLH. (Go up in separate groups to avoid chaos; stop by the red light)
3. Gather on top, please don't block the traffic.
4. Finish with Portola loop: Recovery ride back to the park.
